  "text": "Animals were treated as described above with 10-15 IU eCG. After isolating the ovaries, large FEOs were excised under a stereomicroscope [CITATION_1] . The FEOs (20-25 per dish) were cultured for 2 h in culture medium described above, with or without 5 g/ml of hCG (CR-121 from the National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases, Bethesda, MD). The dishes were placed in a tightly closed culture chamber (MIC-101, Billups-Rothenberg Inc., Del Mar, CA) and then flushed with O 2 /N 2 (1:1). At the end of the culture, the oocytes were collected by puncturing the follicles.",
